<section style="padding:72px 0">
  <div class="about-section">
    <div>
      <div class="about-label">About the Portal</div>
      <h2>Unlocking the genetic heritage of Philippine rice</h2>
      <div class="about-accent"></div>
      <p>
        The 1001 Philippine Rice Genome Portal is a Tripal-powered bioinformatics
        platform developed to catalogue, manage, and share whole-genome sequencing
        data of rice varieties collected across the Philippine archipelago.
      </p>
      <p>
        Built in collaboration with UP, IRRI, DA-PhilRice, and partner agencies,
        this resource supports research in varietal improvement, disease resistance,
        climate adaptation, and conservation of indigenous rice germplasm.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-cards">
      <div class="acard">
        <h4>Genomics Data Repository</h4>
        <p>Whole-genome sequences, SNP variants, and structural annotations for 1,001 rice accessions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="acard green">
        <h4>Bioinformatics Tools</h4>
        <p>BLAST search, JBrowse genome browser, and genotype search microservice integration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="acard gold">
        <h4>Open Access</h4>
        <p>Freely available data supporting breeding programs, conservation, and food security research.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

